TopicTitle: Many copies of stock fuel tanks in the R&D techs

Articles.Content:
the question.

I a, sorry, Why do I have "hundreds of copies of some of the stock fuel tanks showing in the appropriate tech nodes in the R&D Tech nodes. For instance in Basic Rocketry I am seeing at least 500 copies of FL-T100 fuel tank in the available parts list in the R&D Tech node. And in General Rocketry I am seeing 200-300 FL-T200 tanks in the Available parts list in the R&D Tech node."

So what I see when I open the R&D and look at the Basic Rocketry Tech Node, is a few parts (That are supposed to be there) and a FL-T100 fuel tank that is then repeated about 500 times. In other words I see a capsule, an engine, a wing part and 499 FL-T100 fuel tanks that have now been unlocked.

I don't see any other effect in the game in other areas, and am not sure if its just a video glitch, or if every time I a start the game or visit the R&D its adding more parts to the list. I am sure when I first started the save, they did Not have any extra copies of the tanks in the nodes.

The 2nd question

Which Squad file did you want me to check the integrity of? Do you mean for the FL-T100 Fuel Tank file in the Squad Directory?  That seems unlikely as it would involve multiple files as its appears to be all the FL-T tanks (the FL-T100, FL-T200, FL-T400, and FL-T800) So it would have to be the same integrity error effecting all 4 Squad files.  Also I get the game from KSP site, not steam so I cant run a steam integrity check.

I did do a comparison between the Fuel tank files in the Squad folder and the Zip archive I downloaded and they are the same.
